Chemical composition. Flavonolignans such as silymarin, silybin, isosilybin and taxifolin (1.5–3.0%) are the main components reported for 
 S. marianum (
 Wynn, 1999; 
 Porwal et al., 2019); flavonoids (quercetin derivatives); phenolic acids (chlorogenic, caffeic and ferulic acids) (
 Lucini et al., 2016; 
 Valková et al., 2020).
